<para id="para-00011"><title><span class="red-text">Strategy</span></title> Hydrogens on carbon next to a carbonyl group are acidic. In general, a <emphasis effect="italics">β</emphasis>-dicarbonyl compound is most acidic, a ketone or aldehyde is next most acidic, and a carboxylic acid derivative is least acidic. Remember that alcohols, phenols, and carboxylic acids are also acidic because of their –OH hydrogens.</para>
<para id="para-00012"><title><span class="cyan-text">Solution</span></title> The acidity order is (<emphasis effect="bold">a</emphasis>) > (<emphasis effect="bold">c</emphasis>) > (<emphasis effect="bold">b</emphasis>). Acidic hydrogens are shown in red.</para>

